  <TEXT> 
	 <BODY> 
		<DIV1 TYPE="letter"><PB N="[1]"> 
		  <OPENER> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> <ORIG REG="Cherokee">Cerokee</ORIG> Agency</ADDRLINE> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <DATE VALUE="1816-07-06">6th July 1816</DATE></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> 
			 <SALUTE>Sir,</SALUTE></OPENER> 
		  <P>I was at the City when the Convention with the Cherokees was made
			 settling their boundary line: The Secretary of War at that time made a
			 proposition to the Cherokees then there as a deputation, to
			 <DEL><UNCLEAR>unk</UNCLEAR></DEL> cede to the 
		  <NAME TYPE="place"><ABBR EXPAN="United">U</ABBR> States</NAME>all their
		  claims to lands lying west of a line to be run due South from that point on the
		  
		  <NAME TYPE="place">Tennessee <ORIG REG="River">river</ORIG></NAME>
		  which intersected by the Eastern boundary of 
		  <NAME TYPE="place">Madison County</NAME> to the line agreed upon by the
		  said convention. The Cherokee Deputation did not Consider themselves
		  <ORIG REG="authorized">authorised</ORIG> to cede land. Before I came away the
		  secretary told me that a treaty would be ordered to be held in order to obtain
		  some cessions of land from the Cherokees &amp; that I must make my best
		  exertions to effect the Objects. I am now instructed <PB N="[2]"> to open
		  negotiations with the Cherokees for the purpose 
		  <ABBR EXPAN="aforesaid">afordd.</ABBR> and shall omit nothing in my
		  power to obtain the Cession of the lands mentioned also <SIC CORR="the">the
		  the</SIC> <ORIG REG="Cherokee">cherokee</ORIG> lands lying on the North side of
		  the 
		  <NAME TYPE="place">Tennessee <ORIG REG="River">river</ORIG></NAME>.
		  nothing but a cession of the lands first mentioned will put an end to the 
		  <NAME TYPE="person"><ORIG REG="Chickasaw">Chickesaw</ORIG></NAME> claim
		  to the same lands, or most of them; that is one reason why they
		  <ORIG REG="ought">aught</ORIG> to sue. Another reason is they hold too much
		  land, this only retards their improvement in civilization <ORIG
		  REG="another">onother</ORIG> reason is they are in Debt they want money to pay
		  their debts &amp; to make provisions for<UNCLEAR>selcoots?</UNCLEAR> &amp;
		  other improvements &mdash; The Cherokee chiefs particularly those who were in
		  the Army all know &amp; and respect you; your opinion &amp; <ORIG
		  REG="advice">advise</ORIG> would have more effect on them than that of any
		  other man on the face of the earth and should it be in your <PB N="[3]"> way to
		  express your sentiments to 
		  <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="colonel">colo</ABBR> Richard
			 Brown</NAME>&amp; 
		  <NAME TYPE="person"><ABBR EXPAN="Colonel">Colo</ABBR> I Lowry</NAME> on
		  the subject of one or of both these cessions you would lay me
		  <UNCLEAR>under</UNCLEAR> <ORIG REG="very">vary</ORIG> great obligations
		  <ORIG REG="which">whch</ORIG> if in my power I would make proper return in any
		  way you should command me.</P> 
		  <CLOSER> 
			 <SALUTE>I have the honor to be <LB> with greatest respect <LB> 
				<ABBR EXPAN="Your Obedient">Yr Obt</ABBR> Servant </SALUTE> 
			 <SIGNED> 
				<NAME TYPE="person">Return 
				  <ABBR EXPAN="Jonathon"> J.</ABBR> Meigs</NAME></SIGNED> 
			 <ADDRESS> 
				<ADDRLINE> 
				  <NAME TYPE="person">Major 
					 <ABBR EXPAN="General">Genl</ABBR> Andrew
					 Jackson</NAME></ADDRLINE> 
			 </ADDRESS> </CLOSER> 
		</DIV1> 
